3.Why is DNS important before communication begins?  
=Computers communicate using IP addresses, not domain names. DNS translates human-readable names like "google.com" into IP addresses like "142.250.77.46". Without DNS resolving the name first, your device wouldn't know where to send the request, it's like needing a phone directory before you can make a call.
